8:
Not giving up, are we? This is where
things come to an end!
13:
...What? Why... are you looking at me
like that?
17:
Wait, wait! What is the meaning of
this?!
28:
...Dammit. I can't get that face out of
my head...
32:
No matter how skilled a ninja you
may be, coming to the Commission
alone was quite reckless.
34:
Given the circumstances, I have a
few questions—
39: I don't have time for this.
42:
Hmph, I figured it wouldn't be that
easy.
45:
Those blades... Where did you get
those?!
49:
It seems like you know more than
enough.
52:
Yakumo! Give us those blades... And
your life!
67: You saved me back there. But... why?
73:
I told you, didn't I? I have some
questions for you. Plus, you weren't
the only one who was attacked!
76:
...Very well. I have questions of my
own.
79:
...I'm searching for Orochi's blade to
be granted an audience. Do you
know where I can find it?
82: I see... So that's your goal.
85:
But enough chitchat, I highly
suggest we get out of here!
90:
Get a move on, Alk! That cocky
diviner needs our help—you know he
wouldn't ask for help unless he
REALLY needed it!
109:
Someone who's been caught up in
something bigger than all of us. As
you can tell, he's a ninja.
114:
It's Yakumo... I'm a "fugitive" ninja,
just so you know.
116:
I'm searching for Orochi's blade to
be granted an audience. Do you
know where I can find it?
120:
Orochi's blade? You mean that old
geezer?
125: Please, tell me everything you know.
129:
...Suizen, what exactly are you
getting us into?
140:
After the incident with Orochi, spies
that were still loyal to the Grand
Diviner rebelled.
143:
And they tried to summon creatures
that resembled Orochi... But it
seemed like Yakumo here put a stop
to that.
145:
...That is, until they ran off with a
sacred demon blade handed down
by the shogunate.
150:
What?! Anything with the word
"demon" in it sounds like bad news...
154:
As for the missing person, it seems
like it's someone that Yakumo met
during his run-in with those
creatures.
157:
And to meet that person again, he
needs the demon sword... Did I get
that right?
167:
You don't look like the talkative type,
but couldn't you have at least
explained that yourself?
176:
I don't mind lending a hand. Besides,
you seem like someone who will
repay his debts.
181:
Just look at that! He's already
scurrying away!
186: This person you're seeking... Who is it?
191:
It was a girl... She was carrying a
mirror... But the one thing that stuck
out about her was her smile.
193:
It was like a smile that could pierce
through the dead of night... And
wrap me in its warmth.
196:
Why me? Why did she smile at me?
It's been driving me crazy this whole
time.
200:
Understood. Then we'll help you find
her.
205:
...Are you sure about that? I have a
bad feeling about this.
208:
Yes. Yakumo reminds me a lot of
Inaho.
213:
...Thank you. I feel like this will lead
me closer to her.
218: Hey Suizen, is that okay with you?
223:
If you can keep Yakumo safe, then
it's fine with me.
225:
But those who scheme to resurrect
Orochi will not give up so easily. We
will have to be ready to act any time.
228:
Can I count on all of you to be there
to help?
234: Of course! Is that even a question?
237: You know we've got your back.
241:
I will also help. I also happen to be
knowledgeable about their ways.
247:
Then it's decided. Welcome aboard,
Yakumo.
258:
Yakumo may appear fine on the
outside, but I'm worried about what
he's hiding. Can you keep a close
eye on him?
